0.A.2 Dataset
The market data used in our experiments were generated using the Qlib framework666https://github.com/microsoft/qlib. All methods were trained and evaluated in the same manner. To avoid potential data leakage, we adopt a clean data-splitting strategy for AlphaAgent and RD-Agent-Quant during factor mining. Specifically, the training data are further split into 2008-01-01 – 2012-12-31, 2013-01-1 – 2013-12-31 and 2014-01-01 - 2014-12-31 for training, validation and backtesting in mining stages. After all factors are generated, we revert to the original train/validation/test split to train the multi-factor models and backtest, ensuring a fair and leakage-free evaluation.
